subject: p19759491
Findings: As compared to the previous radiograph, the patient has received a pectoral pacemaker. The course of the pacemaker leads is unremarkable, there is no evidence of fracture or displacement. The signs indicative of mild pulmonary edema, present on the previous examination, have decreased. No evidence of pneumothorax. Unchanged mild retrocardiac atelectasis and moderate cardiomegaly. Status post sternotomy.
